If a PM Work Order must be deferred, a PM Result of DEFER is recorded, and a value is added to describe the reason for deferral. Examples of reasons for deferral include: - · Asset could not be located - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out A deferred Work

and a value is added to describe the reason for deferral. Examples of reasons for deferral include: - · Asset could not be located - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out A deferred Work Order may be continued to completion if a missing Asset is found within the time frame in which the Work Order must be performed. Otherwise, the Work Order will be closed with a PM result of deferred, with narrative describing the reason. For more information about this process, please go to Appendix A -Defer Work Business Process to view the flowchart and process narrative. ## User Roles and Responsibilities The audience for this training includes the following user roles: | Role | Responsibility | |---------------------|--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | FM Admin | Rec

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------| | FM Admin | Receives, classifies and disposes building service equipment (BSE) Assets; reviews and approves Work Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance); approves PMwork deferrals; creates Job Plans | | FM Supervisor | Reviews and evaluates Service Requests; plans and approves work; monitors and assigns Work Orders to FMTechs in their Responsible Shops. | | FMTech | Performs work and completes Work Orders; identifies need to defer work; updates PM work status | | FM Work Order Clerk | Reviews and evaluates Service Requests; receives, classifies and disposes building service equipment (BSE) Assets; reviews and evaluates Service Requests; plans and approves work and assigns Work Orders to FM shops; creates PMs (preventive maintenance) | | HTMAdmin | Classifies Assets; reviews and approves Work Orders;

ws and evaluates Service Requests; plans and approves work and assigns Work Orders to FM shops; creates PMs (preventive maintenance) | | HTMAdmin | Classifies Assets; reviews and approves Work Orders; creates PMs (preventive maintenance); approves PM work deferrals; creates Job Plans; determines need for decontamination/sanitization of turned in Assets | | HTMTech | Performs work and completes Work Orders, identifies need to defer work; updates PMwork status; completes decontaminates/sanitizes Work Orders on turned in Assets | | HTMTech Plus | Performs work, identifies need to defer work, and updates PMwork status, work reassignment | ## Learning Objectives - · Defer a PM Work Order - · Introduce when a PM Work Order is deferred - · Notify the EIL Official, as needed ## Agenda | Topic | Estimated Time | |----------------------------------|------------------| | Introduction | 5 min | | Defer PM Work Order | 15 min | | Notify EIL Official if Warranted | 15 min | | Review | 05 min | | TOT

timated Time | |----------------------------------|------------------| | Introduction | 5 min | | Defer PM Work Order | 15 min | | Notify EIL Official if Warranted | 15 min | | Review | 05 min | | TOTAL: | 40 min | ## ACRONYMS USED IN THIS LESSON | Acronym | Description | |-----------|-----------------------------| | EIL | Equipment Inventory Listing | | PM | Preventive Maintenance | ## DEFER A PM WORK ORDER If a PM Work Order must be deferred, a PM Result of DEFER is recorded and a value is added to describe the reason for deferral. Examples of reasons for deferral include: - · Asset could not be located - · Asset is out of service - · Asset is loaned out NOTE: If the missing Asset is found within the window for finishing the Work Order, return to the Execute Work process. If the reason for the deferral does not change, the Tech may complete the Work Order and record a note explaining the circumstances. - Step 1.
